People living in around Pietermaritzburg and Durban, in KwaZulu-Natal, have reported feeling a tremor late on Wednesday night. Volcano Discovery reported an unconfirmed earthquake or seismic-like event: 6.5 km north of Scottburgh, on the south coast of KwaZulu-Natal, at 9.47 pm on Wednesday. The Council for GeoScience said there was no information on the alleged tremor or earthquake, from its monitoring systems. Many Durban and some Pietermaritzburg residents took to social media on Thursday morning to share and ask others if they also felt the earth tremor.  